<subSubSection id="C30AAEC6FFC23C48668F33D6FF2B7617" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BAFFD4DFFC23C48668F33D6FF2B7617" blockId="14.[108,1213,337,1335]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
ETYMOLOGY: The specific epithet is from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B964215FFFC23C4864C133D6FF537631" box="[748,818,1271,1296]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">penna</emphasis>
(wing, feather) and 
<emphasis id="B964215FFFC23C48623133D6F83E7630" box="[1052,1119,1271,1297]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">brevis</emphasis>
(short), referring to the shortened wing that characterizes this species.
</paragraph>
